<plot>How well do we remember the war? Is it hard for us talk about it? Do we start remembering suddenly when talking about it? Interrogation investigates the trauma, but not aiming at human pain. On the contrary, this film attempts to open the abysses of the war denial, which have become a dominant, but silent dimension of everyday life in the post-war Bosnia And Herzegovina.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?264921</url></doc>
